caption: Really tasty 100% certified halal meat!! Friendly staff, fast and easy service how much more can you ask for? They have 2 locations one in Long Island and one in Manhattan. Both are delicious!

My go to for burgers. Prefer the classic burger over the holy burger. Absolutely love the fries.
Nothing like the one in Manhattan. Test less cold burger petty.

terrible customer service
2nd location. Their burgers are consistently excellent. Cheesesteaks made with real shaved rib eye. My kids absolutely love their tenders.. To top it off, everything's halal.
I walked in and walked right out. The place and the kitchen looked very dirty. How can you eat in that place? I am not sure what all the hype is about.
Good food but a little pricey for small portions
The food is average to Good

Had the Holy Burger double and the Cheesesteak with French Fries.   The fries were enough for 4 people and came with 2 dipping sauces.  Burger was very tasty.   Cheesesteak was delicious and spicy.   Even gave us 2 complimentary cup of Chocolate soft serve.   I added the fruity pebbles to mine, which I reccomend.   Haven't tried the Holy Chicken or the Chicken tenders but both come highly recommended.
Clean and friendly environment. Food was delicious 🤤
Delicious food & excellent service 👌👌👌
Unbelievably good... Awesome service, great establishment, friendly workers... Highly recommend!
Yummy french fries and tasty chicken sandwich!
Best halal cheeseburger
Excellent food, easy parking
I dont like at all
excellent burgers, sliders just like in the city
Amazing food. Amazing customer service
best new york cheesesteak of all timee 🥰🥰
Great customer service,the food was delicious, felicia was friendly... the steak with cheese was so good...
Amazing service from Felicia very welcoming will come again
Excellent experience but service is very very slow. They should hire more people
NYC cheesesteak: disliked the taste Onion rings & fries: good Hot dog: average Their signature sauces: really good
I love the Impossible Burger...can't eat the fast foods anymore
My first time there and the burger was great.
Its okay.
Holy Chicken never disappoints! 🔥🔥🔥💪🏼💪🏼
HMS/SBNY certified - Zabihah meat  Got the chopped cheese and fries here.  Fries are salty but crunchy. Chopped cheese is great as well, generous portion of meat.
I tried grill chicken sandwich from this place and I must say it was delicious. 5 stars from me. Keep up the good work guys.
Best halal food in the city
Excellent burgers! The service was fast and efficient. Didn't get to sit in and enjoy due to COVID restrictions.
I'll hold on to my review for another couple of months,  won't be fair. Store opened for business in difficult times.
New concept excellent food and customer service.
Best cheese steak in NY, hands down. The classic burger with 2 - 2oz patties are the way to go. Food is great and service is top notch. Highly recommend trying this place.
Good new place to eat owners are very nice place is clean and food is great and price is affordable
Excellent food. Thanks rizzu bhai. Great customer service. Discount code “Dekalb25”
Amazing burgers amazing service all around great dining experience

While the place is known for their burgers which are good, the chicken sandwich might even be better.  Slightly spicy, fried but not salty and a good size portion served on toasted brioche bun.  Haven't had this type of sandwich for a while.
Best hot dogs ever also great service

There customer service is very good.. and felicia is a very wonderful and helpful person.. she know how to take care of her customers and make them happy... my boyfriend and I went their and we are very satisfied with the way she took care of us..and there food and shakes are very delicious..
Halal food Best price Nice people serving in the Heart of Asian American community
Delicious food! I'm glad they are close to me now.
Fast and clean service. So much flavor in their holy chicken burger! Definitely try their seasoned fries!

I like the city location way better. That one doesn’t take as long to serve people even if it’s busy. The cashier is very friendly at this elmont location but the kitchen seems disorganized. It took very long to get my order out. I wish that the manager or management would improve. I would love to come again if that happens. A extra star for the amazing food. The young man cooking I do not know his name but he is a great cook. He is probably around the age of 17. He always has a hat on backwards. I have seen him at the city location as well. Make sure to ask for him to make your order he is very good.

Delicious food but they need more workers in the front. It doesn’t feel welcoming due to only one young lady working at the front. I loved the holy chicken burger. It was so good. I would have tried the shake but it would have took a while since they only have one person in the front working. Management needs to be better but props to the cooks. The food is AMAZING.
The Impossible Burger tasted great!!
The food is very flavorful. Would recommend trying their cheesesteak. They also have many good side options. And the fries were very well seasoned.

I ordered a mix of 6 sliders, 3 chicken and 3 beef and a strawberry milkshake. Both types of burgers were delicious! The 'holy' sauce has a great kick,not to spicy but just the best enhancement to the burgers. I will definitely go back to try other items.
Delicious food good service however you have to wait for a long time

Where to begin? New location but same great taste of food and service. Holy Cow (Elmont) is absolutely a place where you want to go and have hands down, the best 100% Hand Slaughtered (Zabihah Halal) food. You won't be disappointed. My personal favorites are the Holy Chicken, Holy Burger, N.Y.C. Cheesesteak, and Holy Tenders. Mmm, so delicious. I have shared some photos to give you a sneak peak. They make all food items to your personal liking, so they won't mess up for some picky food eaters.  They will soon be having a breakfast menu. I got myself a preview of it and man, was it good...stay tuned...May Allah SWT give all the Holy Cow locations blessing and much much continued success. Ameen.

I went there yesterday ordered the 6 slider box. I requested 3 to be chicken and other 3 burgers. I was super pleased with the taste and texture of the beef 🍔 🔥 🔥  and sauce choice 😋 . The chicken sliders on the other hand not much taste just chicken cutlet cut into a squarish shape and put in bun. Please chef do some magic I want to support my community but feel obligated to share so you can make things right so my belly can be content. FYI I’m coming for those 🍔, sliders weren’t enough 👍
Welcome to elmont, Cheese Stake Sandwich was good.

Great burgers. Big and delicious. Many many options, and very reasonable prices. French fries / Shakes are amazing!  The place has a really nice vibe and last but not least, the staff was super nice. Definitely a must if you love burgers! #GameChanger #BestBurgerLI
The food is great. The sliders are a great option if you don’t want to fill up on a full sized burger and want to try the other sides with it instead.

Excellent customer service. The chicken tenders were perfectly tender and the fries were nice and crispy and full of flavor. They also have other good side options like the sweet potato tots and onion rings.

I visited the manhattan location a few times and it was SO GOOD. I was happy and even more pleased at this location when I placed my order. My favorite has always been the holy burger. I also recommend the N.Y cheesesteak. It was absolutely delicious. So happy this place has opened and it’s closer to me. Will be here often....
Loved the first Manhattan Location, now got a Holy Cow closer to home. Highly recommend the Philly Cheese Steak you wont be disappointed 😍

Delicious Food. Great Customer Service. Cashiers are super friendly the two young ladies are very friendly and helpful. My personal favorite is the holy chicken and tenders. It was a little busy but it was so worth the wait. You won’t find food like this anywhere! Will be back for many more burgers.
Great Place. I loved the food and great customer service. I do not agree with any of the negative reviews because I had a great experience! Highly Recommend. Favorite Halal Burger Spottt.
The establishment just opened and their food is amazing HIGHLY RECOMMEND TO OTHERS!!food is fresh and packaging and service is perfect.

Very bad experience... It look 40 mins for our order to be ready and once we got it, the fries were stale and the burger buns were cold. Our burgers were missing tomatoes too. The whole vibe of this place was gloomy and weird too (compared to the original location).. I don’t think they were ready to open. Hopefully they improve on everything cause the location in the city is very good!
The food was great and made really fast overall amazing experience burger wasn’t dry and had taste quality foods HIGHLY RECOMMEND TRYING IT OUT
I tried their holy chicken burger and it was absolutely delicious! You will not regret trying this place out.
This is a great place with an excellent menu. A must-try for all halal food lovers!!! Helpful staff and an overall 10/10 service.
Mashallah Amazing food and there quality they never let me down so far
Fast service and awesome food! We got the chicken and beef sliders, fries and Philly cheesesteak. Everything was great and loved the sauce on the chicken slider.
Glad they have a location near me now!

So happy that they have a new location in the LI area. A good addition to the LI Halal food scene with more American tasting burgers and sandwiches and certified hand slaughtered good quality meat. I loved the Philly cheesesteak, the Holy Chicken sandwich, the French fries, and the onion rings. Their sauces are also really tasty. Lots of seating and easy parking. Overall great experience!
My family and I went here the food there was so so good ! And the cashier service was excellent . She was so friendly. Highly recommend!
Every thing is perfect. Most important 100% halal
I had the hotdogs and fries, which were really good!

I’m not sure why everyone is bashing this place but the food to me was great and I’ve ate at countless burger joints the classic burger was nice and juicy and the buns were grilled nicely and there burgers actually held up very well compared to other spots where the burgers just crumble apart.. none the less this a great spot and I think everyone should give it a chance !

In response to people complaining about the interior, you can't sit there and eat anyway so why complain about it? The food, however, is AMAZING! I LOVED the burger and chicken sandwiches. Everything was packaged well. Would def go back! Highly recommend.
Delicious burgers and packed so perfectly to go! Didn’t get soggy and flavor was on point! High quality, highly recommend!

Excellent food. Their Holy Chicken sandwich is a marvel to have and their tenders are perfection. The chopped cheese wasn't too shabby either, but I've been recommended the cheesesteak... will definitely be coming back for that!
So glad they finally opened up a zabiha halal joint here. Food was great looking forward to going having the holy burger n chicken again. Food and service was excellent
Food was awesome! Favorite burger spot !
Great Experience! Delicious Food. Highly Recommend Holy Burger.

This is a new location. I called them before going in to make sure they are open and have everything on the menu to try with my group. Went in and they ran out of burger buns. A bad start for this business. Traveled far to try this place. Make sure you make them double check if they have what you want!

Don’t bother going here anytime soon. The restaurant isn’t even complete. Concrete floors, walls. The whole look is depressing. I thought the food would make up for the ambience, I was wrong. The burger bun tasted stale, the fries were cold. They don’t even sell soda yet except for the flat bottled Fanta which I exchanged for a water later. Overpriced for low quality food. Extremely disappointed.

They just opened last Friday, seems like a soft opening as things are still being setup.  I ordered a classic burger with chicken tenders.  The price was good and everything tasted decent.   Not the best burger I’ve had but it’s pretty good.

For an established restaurant, opening multiple locations the food was below nasty. Burger bun was dry and cold. They didn’t follow directions correctly and were missing French fries from the menu. Soggy tator tots was my only side option. Giving them an extra star for serving halal food but I guess they use that to stay in business.
